│  *   **Limited Access to Proprietary Designs**: The report primarily relies on publicly available information, including open-source projects and academic   │
│  papers. Proprietary designs from closed-source projects are not accessible, potentially limiting the comprehensiveness of the architectural overview        │
│  (Architectural Blueprints for Autonomous LLM-Powered Research Agents, confidence_level: High).                                                              │
│  *   **Domain Specificity**: Case studies like Voyager (Minecraft) and AlphaCode (competitive programming) provide valuable insights, but their specific     │
│  domains may limit the direct generalizability of their behavioral patterns to all types of autonomous AI research agents (Behavioral Design Patterns in     │
│  Advanced AI Agents: Case Studies of Voyager and AlphaCode, confidence_level: High).                                                                         │
│  *   **Speculative Nature of Emerging Patterns**: Discussions of future patterns, such as Continual Learning Architectures or Theory of Mind for Agents,     │
